## Propagating Trace Context Across RabbitMQ

The core issue: RabbitMQ doesn't automatically carry W3C `traceparent`/`tracestate` headers. You must **inject** context into message headers on publish and **extract** it on consume.

### Service A — Publisher (Inject)

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Create an ActivitySource for your app
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Orders");

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderPublished", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context into message headers
if (Activity.Current != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = Activity.Current.Id;          // W3C trace ID
    props.Headers["tracestate"]  = Activity.Current.TraceStateString ?? "";
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

### Service B — Consumer (Extract + Link)

```csharp
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Orders");

// In your consumer callback:
void HandleMessage(BasicDeliverEventArgs ea)
{
    ActivityContext parentCtx = default;

    if (ea.BasicProperties.Headers?.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw) == true)
    {
        var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])raw);
        ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentCtx);
    }

    // Start a new activity linked to the producer's trace
    using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
        "OrderConsumed",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext: parentCtx);   // ← this joins the distributed trace

    // ... process the order
}
```

### Wire Up OpenTelemetry (Program.cs — both services)

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Orders")   // or "ServiceB.Orders"
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

### Why this works

| Step | What happens |
|---|---|
| **Publish** | `Activity.Current.Id` is the W3C `traceparent` string (`00-<traceId>-<spanId>-<flags>`). You stash it in a RabbitMQ header. |
| **Consume** | You parse that header back into an `ActivityContext` and pass it as `parentContext`, so the consumer's span becomes a **child** of the producer's span — same trace ID. |

### If you use MassTransit or NServiceBus

Both already propagate trace context automatically via message headers — no manual injection needed. If you're using the raw `RabbitMQ.Client` library, the manual approach above is required.
